}}&lt;/ref&gt; One of his secretaries concluded that John was &quot;a great man in temporal things, but a complete failure and worthless in spiritual things.&quot;&lt;ref name=mccabe/&gt;

==Numbering issues==
{{main|Pope John (numbering)}}
He should not be confused with [[Pope John XXIII]] of the twentieth century. When [[Pope John XXIII|Angelo Cardinal Roncalli]] was elected and became Pope John, there was some confusion as to whether he would be ''John XXIII'' or ''John XXIV''; he then declared that he was John XXIII to put this question to rest. There was no [[Pope John XX|John XX]]; for example, Gibbon refers to the antipope John as John XXII.

