      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Anglo-Saxon society}}
'''Anglo-Saxon monarchs''' were the rulers of the various kingdoms which arose in [[Anglo-Saxon England|England]] following the withdrawal of the Romans in the fifth century.  The most prominent kingdoms were Kent, Sussex, Wessex, Mercia and Bernicia, each recognising their own monarch.  After a considerable period of time and fluctuations in power balance, [[Alfred the Great]] of Wessex was recognised by the other kingdoms as the premier English king.

==Anglo-Saxon kings==
* See the [[:Category:Anglo-Saxon monarchs|Anglo-Saxon monarchs category]].

===[[Wessex]] kings===
* See [[List of monarchs of Wessex]]

===[[Kingdom of the East Angles|East Anglia]] kings===
* See [[List of monarchs of East Anglia]]

===[[Kingdom of Essex|Essex]] kings===
* See [[Kingdom of Essex]]

===[[Kingdom of Kent|Kent]] kings===
* See [[Kings of Kent]]

===[[Mercia]] kings===
* See [[List of monarchs of Mercia]]

===[[Northumbria]] and Northumbria subkingdoms kings===
* See [[List of monarchs of Northumbria]]

==Anglo-Saxon England [[heptarchy]]==
The separate [[monarchy|kingdoms]] which made up Anglo-Saxon [[England]] were:
* [[Kingdom of Kent|Kent]]
* [[Northumbria]]
* [[Wessex]]
* [[Kingdom of Essex|Essex]]
* [[Kingdom of Sussex|Sussex]]
* [[Mercia]]
* [[Kingdom of the East Angles|East Anglia]]

===Subkingdoms of Northumbria===
* [[Bernicia]]
* [[Deira (kingdom)|Deira]]

===Other minor kingdoms===
* [[Kingdom of Ynys Weith|Isle of Wight]]
* [[Kingdom of Suther-ge|Surrey]]
* [[Kingdom of the Iclingas]]
* [[Kingdom of Lindsey|Lindsey]]
* [[Hwicce]]
* [[Isle of Wight|Whitghar]]

