      <comment>/* From actinium to neptunium */ + possible date of introduction of the name actinide</comment>
      <text xml:space="preserve">[[File:Nagasakibomb.jpg|thumb|The [[Fat Man|atomic bomb]] [[Atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki|dropped on Nagasaki]] had a [[plutonium]] charge.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.cfo.doe.gov/me70/manhattan/nagasaki.htm The Manhattan Project]&lt;/ref&gt;]]
The '''actinide''' or '''actinoid''' ([[IUPAC nomenclature]]) series encompasses the 15 [[chemical element]]s with [[atomic number]]s from 89 to 103, [[actinium]] to [[lawrencium]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/4354/actinoid-element Actinide element], Encyclopedia Britannica on-line&lt;/ref&gt; The actinide series derives its name from the [[group 3 element]] [[actinium]]; although actinoid (actinide) means &quot;actinium-like&quot; and therefore should exclude actinium, it is usually included in the series for the purpose of comparison.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite book|last=Connelly|first=Neil G.|coauthors=et al.|title=Nomenclature of Inorganic Chemistry|publisher=[[Royal Society of Chemistry]]|location=London|year=2005|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=w1Kf1CakyZIC&amp;pg=PA52|page=52|chapter=Elements|isbn=0854044388}}&lt;/ref&gt; Only [[thorium]] and [[uranium]] occur in more than trace quantities in nature; the other actinides are [[synthetic elements]].&lt;ref name=g1250&gt;Greenwood, p. 1250&lt;/ref&gt; The actinides are usually considered to be [[f-block]] elements; they show much more variable [[valence (chemistry)|valence]] than the [[lanthanides]]. All actinides are [[radioactive]] and release energy upon radioactive decay; uranium, thorium, and [[plutonium]], the most abundant actinides on Earth, are used in [[nuclear reactor]]s and [[nuclear weapons]].&lt;!-- whereas isotopes of many other actinides are applied in radiomedicine.--&gt; 
{| class=&quot;wikitable&quot;
|- style=&quot;background: #ef99cc&quot;
|&lt;sub&gt;89&lt;/sub&gt;[[Actinium|Ac]]
|&lt;sub&gt;90&lt;/sub&gt;[[Thorium|Th]]
|&lt;sub&gt;91&lt;/sub&gt;[[Protactinium|Pa]]
|&lt;sub&gt;92&lt;/sub&gt;[[Uranium|U]]
